definitions.definition: To agree (in action or opinion); to have a common opinion; to coincide ; to correspond .
examples: The jury concurs with the case put forward by the defence lawyer, that the defendant is undoubtedly innocent.
I do not concur that this is the best way forward.
We do not concur in that particular point.

definitions.definition: To meet in the same point; to combine or conjoin ; to contribute or help towards a common object or effect.

main_definition: To agree (in action or opinion); to have a common opinion; to coincide ; to correspond .
secondary_definitions: To meet in the same point; to combine or conjoin ; to contribute or help towards a common object or effect.
( obsolete ) To run together; to meet .
